net.hudup.core.evaluate

Class MetaMetric

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.hudup.core.alg.AlgAbstract
      • net.hudup.core.evaluate.MetricAbstract
        • net.hudup.core.evaluate.DefaultMetric
          • net.hudup.core.evaluate.MetaMetric
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.rmi.Remote, java.util.EventListener, Alg, AlgRemote, SetupAlgListener, Exportable, Metric, MetricRemote
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    MeanMetaMetric

    @BaseClass
public abstract class MetaMetric
extends DefaultMetric
    Note, the abstract class of Metric interface is {code AbstractMetric}. Three implemented classes of Metric which inherit from AbstractMetric are DefaultMetric, MetaMetric, and MetricWrapper as follows:
    • The DefaultMetric class is default partial implementation of single Metric.
    • This MetaMetric class is a complex Metric which contains other metrics.
    • In some situations, if metric requires complicated implementation, it is wrapped by MetricWrapper class.
    As a convention, this MetaMetric is called meta metric. It contains an array of metrics referred by its internal variables meta.
    Version:
    10.0
    Author:
    Loc Nguyen
